        "title": "7. `agent.py` — CLI subcommands (`db-new`, `db-mark`, `pdf-render`) + `run_claude`",
        "content": "\n**Gaps — entirely untested, and this is where the \"watermark\" dedup logic (a subtle invariant) lives.**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first-run (no marker) uses `since_days` window; group-boundary truncation (`watermark` must land on a `first_seen` boundary, never mid-group) — this is the trickiest bit of logic in the file and has zero coverage.\n- `cmd_db_mark`: invalid ISO string returns exit code 2 and doesn't touch the DB; `--now` vs explicit watermark; neither given → exit 2.\n- `_normalize_ats`: replacements skip `<style>`/`<script>` contents and tag attributes, only touch body text; counts dict accumulates per-label.\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: missing input file → exit 2; Chrome not found → `sys.exit`; Chrome produces non-PDF output → exit 1 with stderr surfaced.\n- `main()` arg-routing: bare `agent.py` → interactive; `agent.py scan` → headless; `agent.py scan -i` → interactive; mode words stop at first flag.\n- `run_claude`: `os.execvp` called for interactive (need to mock — never actually exec in test), `subprocess.call` for headless with the right flags.\n\n```python\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "tests/test_agent.py",
        "content": "import json\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport agent\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef test_cmd_db_new_first_run_uses_since_days_window(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\\nsources: []\\n\")\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"jobs.db\") as store:\n        store.diff([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"T\", url=\"u\")])\n    agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--since-days\", \"1\"])\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 1\n\ndef test_cmd_db_new_truncates_at_group_boundary_not_mid_group(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    db = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db}\\nsources: []\\n\")\n    with Store(db) as store:\n        jobs = [Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i), title=\"T\", url=\"u\")\n                for i in range(3)]\n        store.diff(jobs)  # all share one first_seen timestamp (one group)\n    agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--limit\", \"2\"])\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    # limit=2 can't split the 3-job group -> keeps 0 from this group, truncated=True\n    assert out[\"truncated\"] is True\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 0\n\ndef test_cmd_db_mark_rejects_non_iso_watermark(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\\nsources: []\\n\")\n    rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", str(cfg)])\n    assert rc == 2\n    assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\ndef test_cmd_db_mark_requires_watermark_or_now(tmp_path, capsys):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path / 'jobs.db'}\\nsources: []\\n\")\n    rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"-c\", str(cfg)])\n    assert rc == 2\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_skips_style_and_script_blocks():\n    html = \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>em\\u2014dash</p><script>var x='\\u2014';</script>\"\n    out, counts = agent._normalize_ats(html)\n    assert \"content:'\\u2014'\" in out          # untouched inside <style>\n    assert \"var x='\\u2014'\" in out            # untouched inside <script>\n    assert \"em-dash\" in out                   # replaced in body text\n    assert counts.get(\"em-dash\") == 1\n\ndef test_cmd_pdf_render_missing_input_file(tmp_path, capsys):\n    rc = agent.cmd_pdf_render([str(tmp_path / \"missing.html\")])\n    assert rc == 2\n    assert \"no such file\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"argv,expected_interactive,expected_mode_words\", [\n    ([], True, []),\n    ([\"scan\"], False, [\"scan\"]),\n    ([\"scan\", \"-i\"], True, [\"scan\"]),\n    ([\"scan\", \"--foo\", \"bar\"], False, [\"scan\"]),\n])\ndef test_main_routing(argv, expected_interactive, expected_mode_words, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"agent.py\", *argv])\n    with patch(\"agent.run_claude\") as rc:\n        rc.return_value = 0\n        agent.main()\n    called_words, called_interactive, _ = rc.call_args[0]\n    assert called_interactive is expected_interactive\n    assert called_words == expected_mode_words\n```\n\n---\n\n",
