        "content": "\n1. **End-to-end pipeline run**: real `sources.yaml` → `fetch_all` (mocked at the HTTP layer via `respx`) → `filter_jobs` → `Store.diff` on a real temp SQLite file → `dispatch` (notifiers mocked) → assert final counts. None of this crosses module boundaries today.\n2. **`agent.py db-new` / `db-mark` cycle**: run a pipeline, dump `db-new`, mark with the returned `watermark`, dump `db-new` again and confirm the previously-dumped jobs don't reappear (the exact invariant the group-boundary truncation code exists to protect).\n3. **Store migration on a real legacy DB file** created by an older schema, then run a full pipeline against it.\n4. **Notifier fan-out with a real `dispatch()` call and multiple env vars set simultaneously** (Slack + webhook + SMS all configured) verifying all fire independently.\n\n",
